  <key>1.Ligules surpassing phyllaries by 15–20 mm; cypselae 12–18(–20) mm, including beaks 3–6 mm; pappus bristles plumose on proximal 65–80%, barbs crooked, entangled2. Rafinesquia neomexicana</key>
